In the actual game, White simply hung his queen by playing 16. Qd2.  Instead what follows is computer analysis of how the game should have continued, which I found instructive.
16. Rb1, Ra2 and Qc1 leave white in about as bad of shape.  I will look at 16. Rb1 in another game.
Black can do just as well with 16. ... Bb6 or 16. ... Ne3!
Now  25... Bxb4 26. axb4  completely does not work.
Computer analysis seems to want to take its time and not hurry.  It prefers moves like 27. ... h6 or Rc7, although Bg5 is also O.K.  Since I didn't really understand the other moves, I went with Bg5.
